---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Glow Intel — who we are, why we started, and what we believe about skincare."
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About Glow Intel</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Glow Intel exists because most skincare content is either too basic, too sponsored, or too obsessed with whatever is trending on TikTok this week.
        </p>

        <p>
          We focus on the fundamentals: what ingredients actually do, which products are worth the money, and how to build a routine that makes sense for your skin — not for someone else's.
        </p>

        <h2>What we believe</h2>

        <p>
          Less is more. Not because minimalism is trendy, but because it works. The fewer variables you have in your routine, the easier it is to know what is helping and what is not.
        </p>

        <p>
          Science matters. Not every ingredient with a study behind it is worth buying, but every ingredient worth buying should have a study behind it. We try to separate real evidence from marketing.
        </p>

        <p>
          Honest beats nice. If a product is overpriced for what it does, we will say it. If a trendy ingredient is mostly hype, we will say that too. You deserve the real take, not the PR-approved version.
        </p>

        <h2>What you will find here</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Ingredient breakdowns</strong> — what the science actually says about retinol, niacinamide, vitamin C, and more</li>
          <li><strong>Honest reviews</strong> — no sponsored content, no affiliate pressure to say something is good when it is not</li>
          <li><strong>Versus articles</strong> — direct comparisons so you can make a real decision</li>
          <li><strong>Routines</strong> — practical advice for real skin types, not the airbrushed ideal</li>
          <li><strong>Beauty business</strong> — for anyone thinking about the ecommerce side of skincare</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Questions, pitches, or corrections? We read everything.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
